Penis longer than abdomen, slightly expanded towards apex; apex with distinct cuticular striation, either subacute (
Figure 4e, i, k
) or arrow-shaped (
Figure 4a, c, g
); ostium of variable size (1 to 5× as long as wide); penis apodemes usually shorter than body of penis; endophallus with distinct spiny area, and with or without sclerites consisted on a pyriform central piece and two winged-like lateral pieces (
Figure 4j, l
).

